You're still very beautiful.

789
00:40:04,468 --> 00:40:06,537
Wow, the model answer!

790
00:40:06,604 --> 00:40:07,805
That's not what I…

791
00:40:07,872 --> 00:40:09,407
It's because you work for me.

792
00:40:09,473 --> 00:40:11,409
Just because you're my editor.

793
00:40:12,243 --> 00:40:14,512
That's actually quite cruel, you know?

794
00:40:18,649 --> 00:40:20,484
I want to hear your honest thoughts.

795
00:40:22,086 --> 00:40:23,053
You know,

796
00:40:24,321 --> 00:40:25,156
maybe…

797
00:40:27,358 --> 00:40:29,527
Maybe no one sees me as a woman anymore.

798
00:40:35,466 --> 00:40:36,600
Oh, I'm sorry.

799
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:40,371
I didn't mean to say something
so pathetic.

800
00:40:41,872 --> 00:40:43,507
And in front of you.

801
00:40:44,475 --> 00:40:45,576
I'm sorry.

802
00:40:46,076 --> 00:40:48,312
<i>Tip Number Four: Pretending to cry.</i>

803
00:40:49,146 --> 00:40:50,714
<i>Mom was testing to see</i>

804
00:40:50,781 --> 00:40:53,651
<i>if she still possessed her divine powers.</i>

805
00:40:53,717 --> 00:40:55,853
<i>If her romance tricks she honed back then</i>

806
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:57,822
<i>would still work on men.</i>

807
00:41:47,371 --> 00:41:49,473
Wait a minute!

808
00:41:53,878 --> 00:41:56,580
What are you doing to someone else's man?

809
00:41:56,647 --> 00:41:58,516
Who is this person?

810
00:41:58,582 --> 00:42:01,185
She was loitering
in front of our building.

811
00:42:01,252 --> 00:42:03,320
I asked her what she was doing,
and she said,

812
00:42:03,387 --> 00:42:04,221
"I'm a stalker.

813
00:42:04,288 --> 00:42:07,057
"I'm the best stalker there is.
I'm on my 24-hour shift.

814
00:42:07,124 --> 00:42:09,026
I stalk Soseki Tachibana of Saneisha."

815
00:42:09,093 --> 00:42:11,762
She was funny, so I let her in.

816
00:42:11,829 --> 00:42:13,063
How is that funny?

817
00:42:13,130 --> 00:42:16,467
So we stayed quiet and watched you guys.

818
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:18,969
We were watching closely. But…

819
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:22,306
-I couldn't just watch this happen!
-You've got it all wrong.

820
00:42:22,373 --> 00:42:24,975
I was just testing what would happen
if I cried.

821
00:42:25,042 --> 00:42:26,310
You were testing me?

822
00:42:28,779 --> 00:42:31,015
You too, Soseki!

823
00:42:31,081 --> 00:42:33,117
Why would you enter some woman's house?

824
00:42:33,183 --> 00:42:34,218
Once you've entered,

825
00:42:34,285 --> 00:42:38,289
any woman would fall in love with you!

826
00:42:38,355 --> 00:42:39,723
That's not true at all.

827
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:42,826
Hey. You've got it all wrong!

828
00:42:43,594 --> 00:42:45,429
Let me explain myself.

829
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:47,464
Mom, show them that thing!

830
00:42:47,531 --> 00:42:49,867
The list with 63 tips.
That was Number Four.

831
00:42:50,668 --> 00:42:52,069
Right. Wait a second.

832
00:42:53,871 --> 00:42:55,039
Oh.

833
00:42:57,541 --> 00:42:58,642
Here it is!

834
00:43:00,077 --> 00:43:02,646
See? I was just trying this.

835
00:43:02,713 --> 00:43:04,682
Sally, will you just trust me already?

836
00:43:05,316 --> 00:43:06,917
-Sally?
-Sally?

837
00:43:06,984 --> 00:43:08,285
I'm Saori, so it's Sally.

838
00:43:08,352 --> 00:43:10,621
It's not some woman's house.
She's just a novelist.

839
00:43:10,688 --> 00:43:13,490
This is the home of Ms. Minase.
I'm her editor.

840
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:17,561
I know.

841
00:43:18,829 --> 00:43:21,265
I know that! But!

842
00:43:21,332 --> 00:43:22,833
I was tracking your movements.

843
00:43:22,900 --> 00:43:24,101
You took the Hanzomon Line,

844
00:43:24,168 --> 00:43:25,636
transferred to the Namboku Line,

845
00:43:25,703 --> 00:43:29,139
then you entered this building,

846
00:43:29,206 --> 00:43:31,408
then you didn't move at all.

847
00:43:31,475 --> 00:43:33,510
That's why I got worried!

848
00:43:34,144 --> 00:43:36,347
Are you okay?

849
00:43:36,413 --> 00:43:37,448
I can't…

850
00:43:37,514 --> 00:43:39,583
-I can't breathe.
-She's hyperventilating.

851
00:43:39,650 --> 00:43:41,318
Do you have a bag?

852
00:43:41,385 --> 00:43:43,654
That's been proven to be a bad treatment.

853
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:45,489
Just relax.

854
00:43:45,556 --> 00:43:46,890
Calm down.

855
00:43:46,957 --> 00:43:48,892
Calm down. Breathe out.

856
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:50,561
Mom gets this sometimes.

857
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:51,996
Like when she can't write.

858
00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:55,532
Calm down, okay?

859
00:43:55,599 --> 00:43:57,134
AZUMA

860
00:43:57,201 --> 00:43:59,570
FULL BLADE

861
00:44:13,384 --> 00:44:15,152
I knew it. I'm bad.

862
00:44:18,956 --> 00:44:20,591
I can't do it!

863
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:38,976
I can't see the stars in Tokyo.

864
00:45:02,399 --> 00:45:03,333
So pretty.

865
00:45:04,802 --> 00:45:06,003
Are you awake?

866
00:45:07,671 --> 00:45:09,540
This has a relaxing effect.

867
00:45:11,842 --> 00:45:12,976
I fell asleep?

868
00:45:13,911 --> 00:45:14,878
Soseki said

869
00:45:14,945 --> 00:45:17,181
you have medication you usually take.

870
00:45:18,048 --> 00:45:19,950
You took it and got sleepy.

871
00:45:20,017 --> 00:45:21,085
So you slept here.

872
00:45:23,620 --> 00:45:24,588
I see.

873
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:28,325
I made some lemonade.

874
00:45:28,959 --> 00:45:29,860
You want some?

875
00:45:32,262 --> 00:45:33,163
Thank you.

876
00:45:45,342 --> 00:45:46,343
It's delicious.

877
00:45:50,314 --> 00:45:52,649
-Where's Soseki?
-Oh, Soseki?

878
00:45:52,716 --> 00:45:55,119
Soseki had to work.
He's back at the office.

879
00:46:07,064 --> 00:46:08,198
What?

880
00:46:08,999 --> 00:46:10,167
Hey.

881
00:46:10,868 --> 00:46:13,237
Soseki isn't the one that's making
you a mess.

882
00:46:14,238 --> 00:46:15,272
Love is.

883
00:46:19,376 --> 00:46:21,311
Has Soseki ever done

884
00:46:21,378 --> 00:46:22,679
anything to hurt you?

885
00:46:31,989 --> 00:46:33,724
I get worried for no reason.

886
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:39,229
We live together,

887
00:46:41,231 --> 00:46:42,232
but even then.

888
00:46:45,068 --> 00:46:47,437
I worry because I'm not with him
all the time.

889
00:46:49,873 --> 00:46:51,642
I got hired at Saneisha.

890
00:46:52,242 --> 00:46:54,044
Because I wanted to be near him longer.

891
00:46:55,646 --> 00:46:56,547
Even then…

892
00:46:59,449 --> 00:47:01,485
Just watching him talk and laugh with

893
00:47:03,053 --> 00:47:04,621
female coworkers drives me mad.

894
00:47:09,059 --> 00:47:10,127
It's like someone is

895
00:47:13,564 --> 00:47:16,533
wringing my heart like a rag.

896
00:47:21,972 --> 00:47:24,107
I'm so stupid!

897
00:47:44,995 --> 00:47:46,430
Soseki said

898
00:47:46,496 --> 00:47:49,533
he'd make your favorite stew tonight.

899
00:47:52,569 --> 00:47:53,670
Really?

900
00:47:54,972 --> 00:47:55,873
Yeah.

901
00:48:03,413 --> 00:48:07,417
<i>Sally's about the same age as me.</i>

902
00:48:07,484 --> 00:48:09,553
<i>Honestly, it was moving.</i>

903
00:48:10,053 --> 00:48:12,256
<i>Maybe romance is a war.</i>

904
00:48:12,322 --> 00:48:14,791
<i>For me, it's an encounter with an unknown.</i>

905
00:48:15,893 --> 00:48:18,328
I'll work hard, Mr. Elephant!
Sora Minase is

906
00:48:18,395 --> 00:48:20,097
taking her first adult step!

907
00:48:25,269 --> 00:48:28,272
Wow. Perfect.

908
00:48:28,338 --> 00:48:30,374
Your mom has great taste.

909
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:32,509
True. But I picked too.

910
00:48:33,110 --> 00:48:34,278
We picked together.

911
00:48:35,612 --> 00:48:37,948
You're the cutest you've ever been!

912
00:48:38,015 --> 00:48:40,117
Now, and when you were born.

913
00:48:40,183 --> 00:48:43,287
Don't say things like that, Mom.
I'm not a baby anymore.

914
00:48:43,353 --> 00:48:44,187
Roger that.

915
00:48:47,524 --> 00:48:50,227
I wish you the best of luck.

916
00:48:51,662 --> 00:48:52,996
Thank you, ma'am.

917
00:49:36,506 --> 00:49:37,874
Doctor Wataru!

918
00:49:54,257 --> 00:49:55,359
WE'LL SHOW YOU THE BEHIND THE SCENES
OF <i>DATE MY DAUGHTER!</i>

919
00:49:55,425 --> 00:49:56,393
Now.

920
00:49:56,460 --> 00:49:57,928
What the hell? That's it?

921
00:49:57,995 --> 00:50:00,230
Mom, language. You're too old to swear.

922
00:50:00,297 --> 00:50:03,233
-What the hell? That's it?
-Mom, you're young.

923
00:50:03,300 --> 00:50:04,534
MOM, YOU'RE YOUNG

924
00:50:04,601 --> 00:50:06,903
-Thank you.
-I'm sorry.

925
00:50:24,454 --> 00:50:26,990
THE NOODLES…

926
00:50:27,057 --> 00:50:31,561
THE NOODLES WON'T COME APART

927
00:50:33,030 --> 00:50:35,532
THE TRASH WON'T…

928
00:50:35,599 --> 00:50:39,870
THE TRASH WON'T GO IN!

929
00:50:41,304 --> 00:50:43,040
A FAIL

930
00:50:44,541 --> 00:50:45,409
ANOTHER FAIL

931
00:50:47,544 --> 00:50:48,612
SO CLOSE!

932
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:51,848
A SUCCESS!

933
00:50:51,915 --> 00:50:53,016
Yay!

934
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:56,820
<i>Did you enjoy your date?</i>

935
00:50:56,887 --> 00:50:58,422
<i>-An arranged marriage date?</i>
<i>-He marries.</i>

936
00:50:58,488 --> 00:50:59,756
<i>We can't go to Odaya.</i>

937
00:50:59,823 --> 00:51:01,792
Go on a date with that childhood friend.

938
00:51:01,858 --> 00:51:03,660
<i>I need my own love, or I can't write.</i>

939
00:51:03,727 --> 00:51:06,129
Love is more random.

940
00:51:06,196 --> 00:51:07,798
<i>Will that random love come true?</i>

941
00:51:07,864 --> 00:51:09,933
Let's not get married.

942
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:10,834
Subtitle translation by: Yukimi Ohashi

